<item>
            <title>[HIVE-4251] Indices can&apos;t be built on tables whose schema info comes from SerDe</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-4251</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Building indices on tables who get the schema information from the deserializer (e.g. Avro backed tables) doesn&apos;t work because when the column is checked to exist, the correct API isn&apos;t used.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;hive&amp;gt; describe doctors;                                                                      
OK
# col_name            	data_type           	comment             
	 	 
number              	&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;                 	from deserializer   
first_name          	string              	from deserializer   
last_name           	string              	from deserializer   
Time taken: 0.215 seconds, Fetched: 5 row(s)
hive&amp;gt; create index doctors_index on table doctors(number) as &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;compact&apos;&lt;/span&gt; with deferred rebuild; 
FAILED: Error in metadata: java.lang.RuntimeException: Check the index columns, they should appear in the table being indexed.
FAILED: Execution Error, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; code 1 from org.apache.hadoop.hive.ql.exec.DDLTask
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
